Loan Default Analysis

Natalie LePera

West Chester University | STA551 - HW 04

Dec 2024

1 Introduction

Intro regarding improved accuracy in default prediction models by better classifying population segments. Better repayment probability populations identified for targeted reduced rate loan marketing, improved accuracy in predicting which customers likely to go into default before it happens. Better spending limit adjustments, targeted refinancing and payment plan options.

Variables
Variable Name Variable Type Details
Default Categorical Status of bank loan default
Checking Amount Numeric Amount in borrowers checking account
Term Numeric Loan term in months
Credit Score Numeric Borrowers credit score
Gender Categorical Borrowers gender
Marital Status Categorical Borrowers marital status
Car Loan Categorical If borrower holds a car loan
Personal Loan Categorical If borrower holds a personal loan
Home Loan Categorical If borrower holds a home loan
Education Loan Categorical If borrower holds an education loan
Employment Status Categorical Borrowers employment status
Amount Numeric Loan amount
Saving Amount Numeric Ammount in borrowers saving account
Age Numeric Duration of borrowers employment in months
Number of Credit Accounts Numeric Number of credit accounts in borrowers name
